so a moral philosopher, who gave a lecture series titled Lectures on Jurisprudence, now preserved only in lecture notes. He was unable to realize his plans to create a comprehensive theory of the law and burned all drafts of the work. However, relevant sections of his major works enable the reconstruction of a substantial portion of his ideas in the area of legal theory.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Aug 2020) 0aJurisprudence. 0aLaw and economics. 0aLawxPhilosophy. 4aRechtsphilosophie. 4aRechtstheorie. 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2017z9783110547771oZDB-23-DGC0 cEPUBz97831104894840 cprintz978311048940840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311049119740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110491197423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110491197.jpg  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGCb2017  aZDB-23-DGGb2017